materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"9mk6h","text":"1.0 mm diameter zirconia/silica beads, BioSpec Products, catalog 11079110z","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"acfel","text":"DNeasy Blood and Tissue Kit, Qiagen, catalog 69504","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"frer0","text":"100% ethanol","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"63r9s","text":"Nuclease-free water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2user","text":"2 mL screw-cap tubes with O-ring gaskets","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4j6nh","text":"Nuclease-free low-retention 1.5 mL microcentrifuge tubes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"35ph3","text":"Place placenta tissue samples in screw cap tubes with O-ring gaskets on ice to thaw.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"csur2","text":"Label a 1.5 mL microcentrifuge tube for each placenta sample. Aliquot 1 mL silica beads per tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7lc1c","text":"Add 540 uL Buffer ATL and 20 uL Proteinase K to each tissue. Pour in prepared beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2vmba","text":"Tightly close tubes. Place tubes in Bead Beater,  and tightly close screw-on parts. Homogenize for 2 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a3srh","text":"Incubate lysates with beads in 56C water bath or heat block for 2 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2ti4o","text":"Thaw lysates at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"attbk","text":"Add 600 uL Buffer AL to screw-cap tubes with beads. Vortex and quick spin. Transfer supernatant to microcentrifuge tube with lysate. Discard screw-cap tube with beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ffgvu","text":"Transfer lysate to pre-labeled microcentrifuge tubes. Do not discard beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"c4mke","text":"Vortex lysate until homogenized.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3gf14","text":"Incubate lysates 56C for 10 minutes. Quick spin.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"eoggp","text":"Freeze at -80C or proceed with DNA extraction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5cmee","text":"Prepare columns and buffers. Add 25 mL 100% ethanol to Buffer AW1 and 30 mL 100% ethanol to Buffer AW2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"44rr9","text":"Add one-half volume (approximately 500 uL) 100% ethanol to lysate. Mix thoroughly by vortexing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7vi07","text":"Pipet maximum 700 uL of the mixture to column. Centrifuge at \u003e=6000g for 1 minute. Discard flow through. Repeat this step until all lysate has passed through column.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dq7nt","text":"Add 500 uL Buffer AW1. Centrifuge for 1 minute at \u003e=6000g. Discard flow-through and collection tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2shdi","text":"Place the spin column in a new 2 mL collection tube. Add 500 uL Buffer AW2. Centrifuge for 3 minutes at 20000g. Discard flow-through and collection tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3nhog","text":"While spinning, label 1.5 mL microcentrifuge tubes for elution. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"d0eup","text":"Transfer column to pre-labeled microcentrifuge tubes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9080n","text":"Elute DNA by adding 100 uL Buffer AE or nuclease-free water to the center of the membrane. Incubate for 1 minute at room temperature. Centrifuge for 1 minute at \u003e=6000g. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bkofr","text":"Repeat step 18.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ac2pv","text":"Store eluted DNA at -20C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
